heterogeneous_edge_semantics.description: Real graphs have multiple edge types with different meanings
heterogeneous_edge_semantics.example: In citation networks, edges can mean "similar topic" or "disagreement"

label_noise.description: Real labels are noisy and may not reflect true communities
label_noise.example: WebKB datasets have subjective page categories

feature_label_misalignment.description: Features may be highly predictive without structure
feature_label_misalignment.example: When features alone achieve 80%+, structure adds noise

degree_distribution.description: Power-law degrees cause aggregation to be dominated by hubs

key_finding: Asymmetric gap: SPI achieves 100% accuracy on high-h but 0% on low-h real datasets
